<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910925-0042</DOCNO><DOCID>910925-0042.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Inco Ltd.:   Voluntary Early Retirements   To Be Offered in Ontario</HL><DATE>09/25/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C10</SO><CO>   LABOR N T.N</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)</MS><IN>ALL NON-FERROUS METALS (NFR)COPPER, OTHER NON-FERROUS METALS (ONF)</IN><NS>LABOR, UNIONS, STRIKES, WAGES, RECRUITMENT (LAB)</NS><RE>CANADA (CN)NORTH AMERICA (NME)</RE><LP>   Inco Ltd., Toronto, said it will offer a voluntary earlyretirement incentive program to hourly and staff employees atits Sudbury, Ontario, operations with the goal of cutting 600jobs.   The company said the United Steelworkers of America union,which represents the company's hourly workers, supports theplan.</LP><TEXT>   The staff reduction is necessary because of productioncutbacks and improved efficiency, the company said. It saidthe permanent reduction in employment is expected tocontribute to reducing the company's production costs. Inco,which has 19,000 employees, didn't estimate the cost of theearly retirement program, but said it would save the companyabout US$50 million a year.</TEXT></DOC>